ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates, June 22, 2022/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The UAE strongly condemned the terrorist attacks that recently took place in various cities throughout the Republic of Mali, which resulted in the death of more than 120 innocent people.



The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation (MoFAIC) affirmed that the UAE expresses its strong condemnation of these criminal acts and its permanent rejection of all forms of violence and terrorism aimed at destabilising security and stability in contravention of human values and principles.

The Ministry expressed its sincere condolences to the government and people of Mali and to the families of the victims of this heinous crime.